RESULTS: Associations were sex-specific based on better model fit when including sex interaction terms. Among boys, higher SO2 in utero was associated with lower BMI at {\textasciitilde}13 and {\textasciitilde}15 years, higher SO2 in childhood with lower BMI at {\textasciitilde}15 years, and higher NO2 in childhood with higher BMI at {\textasciitilde}9, {\textasciitilde}13, and {\textasciitilde}15 years using a multi-pollutant model.
